btw, any update about quota reservation part?

Patch Set 8:

Zhi, I have been trying to figure out a good way to handle that.  Because the size is not always given upfront the only way to handle this would be to check the quota after all of the data arrived and reject the upload at that point.  This is safer for sure, but it will waste time/resources.

Another thought would be to check it up front, and at the end.  This is redundant but it would cover the corner cases and have that optimization.

Any thoughts?

Patch Set 15:

iccha: you are correct about the same test name, I will fix that.

Good question with the failed delete.  I think I would have to have specifics to completely address the concern but as of now I think that the quota only applies to storage that glance 'owns'.  In an earlier discussion it was decided that once a location is added to glance that the glance storage driver "owns" that location, and thus when a delete is issued that data is deleted as well.  It is up to the storage driver to properly delete data.  If there are circumstances where a driver cannot properly delete the data then the driver must have some sort of contract with the storage system about cleaning up orphaned data.  But in any case it should be outside of the scope of glance and quotas.
